    <h4 style="color: #1f2937; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700;">Ingredients</h4>
    <p style="color: #6b7280; font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;"><em>Available from Coles, Woolworths, or Chemist Warehouse</em></p>
    <ul style="line-height: 2; font-size: 1.05rem;">
      <li><strong>1 scoop (30g) vanilla whey protein isolate</strong> (Optimum Nutrition, Musashi, or Aussie Bodies from Chemist Warehouse)</li>
      <li><strong>200ml lactose-free milk</strong> (Liddells or Zymil from Coles/Woolworths) - or unsweetened almond milk</li>
      <li><strong>1/4 tsp vanilla extract</strong> (optional, adds depth)</li>
      <li><strong>2-3 ice cubes</strong> (makes it thicker and more satisfying)</li>
      <li><strong>Stevia drops</strong> (optional, if you need more sweetness)</li>
    </ul>

    <h4 style="color: #1f2937; font-size: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; font-weight: 700;">Step-by-Step Instructions</h4>
    <ol style="line-height: 2.2; font-size: 1.05rem;">
      <li>
        <strong>Choose your liquid base:</strong> Lactose-free milk provides more protein and creaminess. Almond milk is lower calorie. Start with milk for better nutrition.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Add to blender:</strong> Pour milk into blender first (liquid first prevents powder from sticking to blades).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Add protein powder:</strong> Add one level scoop of protein powder. Don't add extra - more isn't better in early weeks.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Add ice and vanilla:</strong> Add ice cubes and vanilla extract if using. Ice makes it thicker and more milkshake-like.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Blend on low:</strong> Start blending on low speed for 10 seconds, then increase to high for 20-30 seconds until completely smooth.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Check consistency:</strong> Should be smooth like a thin milkshake. If too thick, add 30-50ml more milk. If too thin, add 1-2 more ice cubes and blend again.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Serve immediately:</strong> Protein shakes separate if left sitting. Drink within 15 minutes for best texture.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Sip slowly:</strong> Take 20-30 minutes to drink. Use a spoon if easier than sipping. Never use a straw (causes gas).
      </li>
    </ol>

